title: Grateful Dead Live at Rubber Bowl, University of Akron on 1986-07-02
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told-> They Love Each Other, Little Red Rooster*, Don't Think Twice It's Alright*, It's All Over Now Baby Blue*, Candyman, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Playin' In The Band-> Desolation Row**-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Box Of Rain

*W Bob Dylan, **Without Jerry. Dylan, Petty and Heartbreakers opened.

reviews.review_text: Summer '86~ I wasn't lucky enough to catch any shows during the summer of '86, but some of the shows are pretty darned' good!  This chasingwilma  upload from is my favorite AUD pull from the Rubber Bowl, and the Candyman, Desolation Row, and Sugar Magnolia are all highlights.  God Bless the Grateful Dead~

A Trip of Firsts This was the 1st Dead that I had ever listened to. I took my 1st ever trip to the Rocky Mountains from the midwest in 1987. My 1st backpacking hike. 1st climbed peak. 1st hot spring. At the end of this wonder filled trip, while waiting to fly home from the Denver airport, I met two flowery girls who kindly helped me pass the time. They had just seen the Red Rocks show. They left me with a tie dye and a cassette of this show. Nothing was ever the same after that! For me, this show will always have the highest rating.
